              "free_text": [
                " K-400 Intense Neutron Generator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A yield 3 - 4 E10 n/(4Pis). The deuteron ion",
                " beam current was up to 180 uA with of an energy of",
                " 250 keV. The solid tritium-titanium (T-Ti) target",
                " used in the generator was approximately 2.59 mg/cm2",
                " thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "About 6 g of ruthenium powder of natural isotopic",
                " composition (purity 99.95%) was pressed into a pellet",
                " (about 20.0 mm in diameter, 1.5 mm in thickness).",
                " Monitor foils of natural niobium foils (purity",
                " 99.99%, 0.1 mm in thickness) of the same diameter as",
                " the pellet were attached in the front and at the back",
                " of each ruthenium sample. Three group such samples",
                " were prepared for irradiation and measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiation was lasted approximately 17 h.",
                " The samples were cooled about 18 days."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A lead-shielded HPGe detector (ORTEC, USA).",
                " The relative efficiency of the detector was 68%, and",
                " the energy resolution was 1.82 keV (FWHM) at 1.33 MeV",
                " of 60Co."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DECAY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Half-life of 95mTc = 61.88 +/- 0.22 d"
